Create A Saleforsce Project
Ctrl+Shift+P -> sfdx -> select (create Project) -> select (standard) -> name the Project

Authorizing Dev Hub
Ctrl+Shift+P -> select (Authorize Dev Hub) 

Creating A Scratch Org
Ctrl+Shift+P -> select (Create A Default Scratch Org)




Commands
Creating A Lightning Web Component
sfdx force:lightning:component:create -n <component_name> -d force-app/main/default/lwc --type lwc

-n: defines name of Lightning web component folder and files.

-d — defines target directory where Lightning web component should be created, must be name lwc

--type — Specifies that you want to create a Lightning Web Component.(Specifies component type)

sfdx force:lightning:component:create -n myFirstWebComponent -d force-app/main/default/lwc --type lwc


.eslintrc: The configuration file, that defines the Salesforce-specific linting rules